Ending this year in the office with my brother @juwanbufford.jb . This year was nothing short of blessed with me dropping a classic album at the top of the year, hearing a song I’m featured in played at the Super Bowl, having album reviews by some of the most respected blogs, headlining my second tour, performing at Red Rocks, touring in Canada, Australia, and New Zealand, started a Label, Dropped a surprise E.P, got to lift with the legendary CT Fletcher and his son at their HOUSE, spoiled my kids per usual and as amazing as all that sounds I still spent a few days in a psychiatric unit. What that meant to me in the grand scheme of things is that no matter HOW amazing things are that I’m DOING, I need to make sure to take care of ME overall. A better me will experience and appreciate these blessings MORE. A better me will LIVE to see these things through HEALTHILY, because not only do y’all deserve a better me, I DESERVE a better me! So here’s a toast to better health, success, self awareness, and LOVE! Happy new year!

Anyone who knows me KNOWS that I have always spoke about the love I have for the Palestinian people. The fact MILLIONS of people have been massacred since 1947 as well as forcing millions to be crammed in a prison like environment is sickening. The way the MEDIA has done these people is just as sickening man. Let me say this, I’m TOTALLY AGAINST the harming of innocent people ESPECIALLY CHILDREN (either way you spin it) and I have close friends who have been impacted by this conflict so I feel it’s my duty as their BROTHER to speak up. When you’re forced to live like this there will always eventually be some sort of public outrage and that’s what I believe what we are witnessing currently. To think that SEVENTY FIVE years of this with no rightful solution is sad. Y’all have my love and support and anything I can do to help I will. Thank you for your love and insight brother @anas.afana.1 you are an amazing brother!✊🏾🇵🇸
